<HEADLINE> No. 5 Arizona 65, California 61  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    BERKELEY, Calif. (AP) -- Loren Woods scored 23 points, including two key
baskets over the final 1:30, and No. 5 Arizona beat California 65-61 Thursday
night in the teams' Pac-10 opener.
</P>
<P>
	   Michael Wright added 15 points and the freshmen backcourt of Gilbert Arenas
and Jason Gardner had 10 points each for the Wildcats (12-2), who won their
conference opener for the third time in four years.
</P>
<P>
	   Arizona coach Lute Olson picked up his 599th career victory. He'll seek his
next one Saturday, when the Wildcats face top-ranked Stanford.
</P>
<P>
	   Nick Vander Laan's 14 points led Cal (9-4), while Dennis Gates and Sean
Lampley added 12 points each.
</P>
<P>
	   The Wildcats were trailing 56-51 when they put together a 7-0 burst, moving
in front 58-56 on a putback and two free throws by Wright.
</P>
<P>
	   Lampley grabbed an offensive rebound and dunked to tie it 58-all but Arizona
scored six straight points, starting with Luke Walton's 6-foot runner in the
lane. Woods had a driving layup off a feed from Gardner and then hit a short
turnaround jumper with 50 seconds remaining.
</P>
<P>
	   Brian Wethers came back with a 3-pointer but that was the last score for
Cal. Gardner made one of two free throws with 18 seconds left and Joe Shipp and
Lampley missed long jumpers for Cal in the final seconds.
</P>
<P>
	   Arizona went in front 51-50 behind an 11-3 run that included 3-pointers from
Gardner and Walton but Cal scored the next six points, starting with a 15-foot
jumper by Lampley to regain the lead.
</P>
<P>
	   Vander Laan scored 10 of his points in the first half, when Cal led 40-35.
</P>
<P>
	   Cal hurt itself by committing 21 turnovers and shot just 35 percent from the
field compared to 44 percent by the Wildcats.
</P>
<P>
	   The Bears outrebounded Arizona 46-31 but were not accurate enough with their
shots off the rebounds to make a difference.
</P>
</TEXT>
