<HEADLINE> Treasury Bond Prices Move Lower  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Treasury bond prices were lower at midday.
</P>
<P>
	   The price of the Treasury's main 30-year bond was down 9-32 point, or $2.81
per $1,000 in face value, around midday, while its yield rose to 6.57 percent
from 6.55 percent late Thursday. Prices and yields move in opposite directions.
</P>
<P>
	   Yields on three-month Treasury bills fell to 5.38 percent as the discount
lost 0.01 percentage point to 5.23 percent. Six-month yields fell to 5.65
percent as the discount fell 0.01 percentage point to 5.42 percent. One-year
yields rose to 6.01 percent as the discount gained 0.01 percentage point to 5.67
percent.
</P>
<P>
	   Yields are the interest bonds pay by maturity, while the discount is the
interest at which they are sold.
</P>
</TEXT>
