<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Higher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LONDON (AP) -- Technology and telecommunications stocks staged a comeback
Friday, reversing a week of declines in most European markets.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Industrial Average posted strong gains throughout the session,
providing an extra boost for bourses.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 606 European companies closed up 2.1 percent at
359.75, while the Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 324 companies in
countries joining the single currency, ended up 3.2 percent at 395.36.
</P>
<P>
	   The telecom sector of the Dow Jones Stoxx Index rose 3.4 percent, while the
technology sector gained 3.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   In domestic markets, the Paris CAC 40 index ended up 1.6 percent at
5,539.61.
</P>
<P>
	   Spain's IBEX-35 share index rose 2.2 percent to 11,102.40 as utilities
GasNatural and Union Fenosa posted strong gains. Union Fenosa rose 5.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   In London, the FTSE 100 gained 0.9 percent to close at 6504.8. Technology
stock ARM Holdings was one of the day's stars and closed up 6.1 percent.
Powergen rose 6.2 percent after the fossil fuel generator said it is in
negotiations to acquire a 49 percent stake in a power plant in southern India.
</P>
<P>
	   Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index reversed four consecutive days of losses, to end
4.7 percent higher at 6,780.96. SAP boosted the index up 18.5 percent after the
company released positive fourth-quarter figures.
</P>
<P>
	   Amsterdam's benchmark 25-share AEX index rose 3.3 percent to 644.86, boosted
by software maker Baan, ASM Lithography, Philips and telecom company KPN.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Stoxx 50 Index finished up 2.5 percent at 4,452.5, while the
DJ Euro Stoxx 50 Index ended up 3.3 percent at 4,648.3.
</P>
</TEXT>
