the Army said it hired a Chicago consulting firm, Jones-Lundin
Associates Inc., to help it select an ad agency for a new contract
that, unlike the existing arrangement, would pay the agency based
on how many recruits it attracts. The Army said Young &AMP; Rubicam is
welcome to compete for the new contract. The agency's current
five-year contract is due to expire in July. Officials said it was
unclear whether that contract would be terminated early.
</P>
