<HEADLINE> Leko Wins Fourth Chess Match  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) -- Opening with a French defense, Hungarian chess
prodigy Peter Leko on Friday won the fourth of six scheduled matches against
Russian world champion Alexander Khalifman.
</P>
<P>
	   Leko, 21, has won two games and has two ties in the exhibition tournament.
By taking a point for each win and half a point for each tie, he leads 3-1 and
will win regardless of the outcome of the next two games.
</P>
<P>
	   After the 53rd move, Khalifman, 33, gave up Friday's match, which lasted
just over 5 1/2 hours.
</P>
<P>
	   ``After I had gained the advantage, I knew it was just a question of
technique when I'd win the match,'' an exuberant Leko said.
</P>
<P>
	   The tournament is sponsored by the German Westfalische Ferngas AG. The
winner receives $10,280 and his opponent gets $5,140.
</P>
</TEXT>
