<HEADLINE> Clinton Chats With Mrs. Barak  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SHEPHERDSTOWN, W.Va. (AP) -- President Clinton popped into a luncheonette
Friday for a cup of coffee and a chat with the wife of Israeli Prime Minister
Ehud Barak.
</P>
<P>
	   Nava Barak had cappuccino while the president had coffee with no sugar as
they chatted in the Pharmacy, a downtown Shepherdstown establishment known for
