<HEADLINE> Kenya Police Looking for Escapees  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) -- Police and prison guards were hunting on Friday for 15
suspects who escaped from a prison in central Kenya, a police official said.
</P>
<P>
	   Deputy police spokesman Dola Ididis said at least 21 suspects charged with
capital crimes ranging from murder to treason scrambled over the prison wall and
a barbed wire fence Thursday evening as guards changed duties at Thompson Falls
Jail in Nyahururu, 100 miles northwest of Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
	   Six of the escapees were captured, Ididis said.
</P>
<P>
	   The private Kenya Television Network said guards shot at least three
escapees dead and several guards were injured in fights with the fleeing
prisoners. Ididis said he could not confirm the report.
</P>
<P>
	   Prison authorities were reported to have ordered an investigation into the
jailbreak.
</P>
<P>
	   Kenyan jails and prisons, notoriously congested and disease-infested, have
been described as inhuman by legislators and human rights groups.
</P>
<P>
	   Although conviction for crimes of murder, cattle-rustling and treason
carries a mandatory death sentence by hanging, no one has been executed in Kenya
for at least a decade.
</P>
</TEXT>
