<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man linked to 1995 killing of Camden girl arrested in Florida  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) - A man who disappeared days after a Camden teen-ager
was found dead in a field in 1995, and who has been linked to the unsolved
killing, was arrested in Florida on unrelated charges of attempted sexual
assault, authorities said Friday.
<P>
	   Prosecutors declined to identify Miguel Figueroa, of Camden, as a suspect in
the killing of Shaline Sequinot, but the arrest was seen by many as a potential
breakthrough in the case.
</P>
<P>
	   "I will never give up hope," said Sister Helen Cole, of Holy Name Church in
North Camden, where the 13-year-old was found sexually assaulted and stabbed to
death. "I couldn't do the work I do without believing this will be resolved."
</P>
<P>
	   Shaline, an honor student, disappeared on Aug. 4, 1995 after riding off on a
borrowed bicycle. She was found dead three days later. She had been sexually
assaulted and stabbed 10 times, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   Last March, detectives traveled to Puerto Rico searching for Figueroa, a
native of the island commonwealth. Posters there said he was wanted for
questioning in Shaline's killing and on a warrant charging him in a sexual
assault case.
</P>
<P>
	   "It paid off. We're glad to have him in custody," said Camden County
Prosecutor Lee A. Solomon.
</P>
<P>
	   Acting on a tip, investigators from Camden and Camden County nabbed Figueroa
in the Tampa area Thursday night with assistance from Florida law enforcement,
Solomon said.
</P>
<P>
	   Figueroa, 29, was being held in Florida pending extradition to New Jersey,
Solomon said. It was not known when Figueroa would return to face attempted
sexual assault charges involving a 14-year-old girl, he said.
</P>
<P>
	   The alleged sexual assault attempts occurred on several dates between
January and April 1995, Solomon said. Authorities have been searching for
Figueroa since October 1998.
</P>
<P>
	   Solomon declined comment on whether Figueroa was wanted for questioning in
Shaline's killing. So far, Figueroa has only been charged with attempted sexual
assault, and could face up to 10 years in prison, if convicted.
</P>
<P>
	   "We don't identify suspects until they are charged," the prosecutor said.
</P>
<P>
	   Shaline's killing struck a nerve in Camden, a city where a record 60 people
were killed that year. Relatives and friends put up bright yellow ribbons to
encourage anyone with information about the killing to come forward.
</P>
<P>
	   "There are people out there who know what happened," said Sister Helen. "I
just hope they have the courage to come forward."
</P>
<P>
	   Authorities have revealed few clues in the murder. Human blood stains were
found inside the school, raising speculation that Shaline was killed there, but
there was not enough blood to determine whether it belonged to her.
</P>
<P>
	   Investigators also revealed in August 1998 that they were searching for at
least two suspects, but did not disclose their identities. An $8,000 reward has
been offered.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-01-07-00 2005 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
