<HEADLINE> 'Puffy' Faces Shooting Lawsuit  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Rap mogul Sean "Puffy" Combs was sued Friday for $50
million by a man who was shot in a Times Square-area nightclub last week.
</P>
<P>
	   Robert Thompson, 38, of Danbury, Conn., alleges he was shot in the right
shoulder by Combs protege Jamal Barrow during a dispute in Club NY on Dec. 27.
</P>
<P>
	   Two other people were wounded in the shooting, and one is suing Combs and
Barrow for $100 million.
</P>
<P>
	   Barrow, 19, has been indicted on weapons and attempted murder charges.
</P>
<P>
	   Combs has said he was not involved in the shooting. He is charged with
illegal possession of a gun that was found in his sport utility vehicle minutes
after he and girlfriend Jennifer Lopez fled the club.
</P>
<P>
	   Thompson sued Combs, Barrow, Club NY and a company that was handling
security at the club.
</P>
<P>
	   Combs' lawyer Harvey Slovis called Thompson's complaint "another in the
unending lawsuits against Puffy Combs, who did nothing that night. It is a
frivolous lawsuit. He is not responsible for what Jamal Barrow does."
</P>
<P>
	   Kenneth Nolan, Thompson's lawyer, said Combs was sued because it is unclear
whether the rapper encouraged Barrow to fire and whether Combs had a gun in the
club. Nolan said that if he learns that Combs did nothing illegal, he will amend
the complaint.
</P>
<P>
	   Barrow's attorney did not return a message seeking comment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
