<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-07 23:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canucks 3, Stars 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    DALLAS (AP) -- Donald Brashear scored the go-ahead goal with 7:03 left as
the Vancouver Canucks rallied to beat the Dallas Stars 3-1 on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
	   Brashear's shot from the from the slot deflected off Stars defenseman Jamie
Pushor's skate and past goalie Ed Belfour.
</P>
<P>
	   Alexander Mogilny scored from the right circle 2:04 later to help the
Canucks win for only the third time in their last 19 games (3-12-4).
</P>
<P>
	   Dallas held a 1-0 lead after two periods on Kirk Muller's power-play goal in
the first period, but Vancouver tied it with 14:45 left on Todd Bertuzzi's goal.
</P>
<P>
	   Garth Snow stopped 31 shots for the Canucks. Snow made a difficult save
against Brendan Morrow with 9:30 left while the Stars were on a power play.
</P>
<P>
	   The Stars had an 11-2 shots advantage in the second period, but Snow kept it
a one-goal game.
</P>
<P>
	   Stars defenseman Brad Lukovich left the game in the first period because of
a mild concussion. Dallas left wing Jere Lehtinen also was sidelined in the
first period by an ankle injury.
</P>
</TEXT>
